DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);
TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$showPartialCredit = 0;

# output the text of the problem

$a = random(2,9,1);
$b = random(2,9,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Find the \( x- \) and \( y- \) intercepts of the graph of
\( y=$a x^2 - $b \). If some solution does not exist, type
\( N \) for both coordinates. Enter the \( x- \) intercept
with the smaller \( x- \) coordinate first.

\( x- \)intercepts are ( \{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\} )
and ( \{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\} )

\( y- \)intercept is ( \{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\} )

EOT

$ans1 = -sqrt($b/$a); 
$ans2 = 0;
$ans3 = sqrt($b/$a); 
$ans4 = 0;
$ans5 = 0;
$ans6 = -$b;

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));
ANS(num_cmp($ans4));
ANS(num_cmp($ans5));
ANS(num_cmp($ans6));


ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
